trend_summary: Industrial and commercial floorspace grew north-west of the corridor, while scattered residential infill filled many central cul-de-sacs. Tree cover thinned around new projects but matured in established streets. Road network saw a few connectors and roundabouts added. Change is steady densification rather than outward sprawl.
notable_changes: Industrial estate enlargement beside the northwest runway corridor
New warehouse/commercial blocks along the western arterial road
Residential infill on remaining vacant lots within central neighbourhoods
Addition of secondary roads and roundabouts improving internal connectivity
Loss of small forest patches in the east-central sector
